rComments: Great professor, always available if you need help.

Prof Abdelrazeq was hands down one of my favourite profs at the University so far. Personally, I hadn't taken maths in three years prior to taking calculus at the university level, and man did he make it interesting, fun and easy to understand. Great prof, would recommend to any student.

Very good teacher! He explained things well and clearly, always making sure to repeat when he saw the class wasn't following. He was available for questions and made us participate during the class, for example by asking questions to see if we had understood the material correctly. The assignments and exams were very representative of the material.
Great prof! Very passionate and nice. Always available to help!

Very very helpful teacher. He is always enthusiastic and trying to involve the class. He has a positive attitude and always has times for questions. However he is sometimes difficult to understand but if you attend class and review the notes you'll be fine. Definitely would recommend taking a class with him to any student!!!

He is the master of mathematics, and should continue to spread his awesome teaching skills upon other students. He is very nice and is willing to interact with the class, which makes the class a lot more fun.
He explains the material very clearly. He is a very good professor except he makes some small and interesting mistakes in class.
Great teacher, very helpful.
Go to class, and you'll do well.

Great teacher who teaches you what you need to know to do well. The material is easy if you pay attention and study. The  professor always has time for questions and will always go over the difficult concepts. No surprises on the exams and questions are always clear

Very good teacher who enjoys what he teaches which clearly shows in the way he talks about the content in class. Only note would be that his accent can be a little hard to understand at the start. Always keeps you up to date with emails and tells you what is on the exam so there are not surprises. Overall one of the best profs i had first year.
Awesome prof! Very helpful and his tests clearly reflect what was covered in class. I recommend him to anyone.
Very good professor and very kind too id recommend him. he also gives good tips on what to study.Study and u will be ok

He is by far the best professor in first year, he always takes at least a 1000 steps to help you out, you will be a head of the other math class material wise and therefore he will have more time to revise before midterms and definitely before your final... He is charismatic and  very interactive with his class. Finally, I recommend this prof.
Super helpful prof. Really passionate about teaching. He wants his students to succeed. Only concern is his writing can be messy and difficult to read. My fave prof this year.

Great professor. He may be unclear sometimes. This professor WANTS you to succeed, he encourages you to go to help sessions and offers help to students all the time. His exam questions are similar to the ones he takes up in class and in the DGD's. I highly recommend taking this professor.
He is interested in teaching and is there when you need help. His notes and examples are very helpful for the exams. Attend the dgd. I highly recommend this prof.
This was a great class. The prof was easy to listen to and understand the material was interesting and easy to study. It was all great.
-Easiest Prof, exam questions are the same or similar to the inclass examples or textbook examples. If u understand how to solve the examples u will get an easy A+.
His clarity was not always good as I didn't find him easy to follow all the time since he couldn't convey what he wanted to say 100% properly. He was, however, interested in teaching as it seemed.
Good prof - explains concepts through lots of examples. Notes are great to study for midterms and final. Very fair exams.
Prof was really good, he explains really well and is approchable.  I would highly recommend him.  His notes are also very useful for the tests and exams.

Cool prof overall. He has a bit of an accent but you get used to it. His midterms and finals were very fair. The questions on the final were very similar to those in the midterms. Go to the DGDs, because they help you absorb what you learned in class. Also, he has partial notes online, so that's pretty cool.
Very helpful proffessor he is always there you will like him very much, very easy examinations.Very fair
